Since the beginning of the year, largely because of an increased world demand for Clarets, and the publicity showered upon the 1959 vintage, the prices in Bordeaux have been going up and

up. The small remaining stocks of 1952s, 1953s and 1955s are either unobtainable or very much more expensive. Soon we will be forced to raise our prices to reflect the higher replacement costs. In our opinion, this offering provides a unique opportunity to lay down some of the fine Chateau bottled Clarets of Bordeaux at prices well below the current market value. And you will also discover here the well matured and delightful 1950s, as well as some of the rare 1949s.
